awd_titl_txt: U.S-Mexico Research:  Studies on (Group 14, Si, Ge, Sn)     Metal Complexes
awd_abstract_narration: This U.S.-Mexico award will support Professor                                   Keith Pannell of the University of Texas at El                                  Paso in a research collaboration with Professor                                 Jorge Cervantes of the Universidad de Guanajuato,                               Mexico.  The objective of the collaboration is to                               synthesize new transition metal complexes                                       containing Si-Sn and Ge-Sn bonds directly bonded                                to the metal atom, and study their                                              photochemistry, reactivity toward base,                                         structures and mass spectrometric properties.                                   The researchers also propose to synthesize a                                    series of metal substituted oligosilyl-siloxanes                                for study of redox and conductivity properties,                                 and incorporation into polymeric siloxane                                       materials.                                                                                                                                                      The synthesis of metal complexes, and                                           photochemical, and structural aspects of the                                    collaborative work will be performed in El Paso,                                while base-induced migrations, oligosilyl-                                      siloxane precursor synthesis, and mass spectral                                 simulations will be performed in Guanajuato.
